message:

title: 820-01700 5V 0Amp liquid
message:

It may work from other model also; need to test.

title: 820-01700 5V 0Amp liquid
message:
i have change the PMIC for 820-01700. I have 5V 0,050A now.
short is remove, I have PPBUS_G3H=12V
I have PP1V8_SLPS2R short too, when I inject 1V I have T2 chip become hot, can I replace it?
I think 'no' 🙃
thanks

title: 820-01700 5V 0Amp liquid
message:
Yes, you can replace it; if you can get compatible version with your SSD size.
Of course, you will lose touch ID function; if you can't get it from the same machine, with replacement T2.
